1/12 Access Modifier private

Access Modifier Private
	- basically, you want to use public methods to access private variables

Local Variables vs. Instance Variales
	-local variables
	- Class attributes

4.9 Value types vs. Reference types
	- if you pass by value then you're just using a copy of the value
	- if you use reference then you are changing the actual value located in memory
	- reference is real, value is a copy

4.10 initializing with constructors